# Local install artifacts — never track these. An afk worktree symlinks its
# node_modules at the main repo's real install; committing that symlink makes it
# self-reference and corrupts main on merge (issue 98).
#
# NOTE: the pattern is slash-less on purpose. `node_modules/` (trailing slash)
# matches a DIRECTORY only — it does NOT match the node_modules *symlink* a
# worktree creates (git treats a symlink as a file), which is the exact artifact
# that reached main. Slash-less `node_modules` matches the dir AND the symlink.
# Covered here (durable, all worktrees) and enforced by the commit +
# merge-preflight guards in code.
node_modules
out
dist

*.log
.DS_Store
tsconfig.node.tsbuildinfo
